  "report": {
    "narrative": [
      "Scheduler pressure (2026-03-01..2026-03-24 window; snapshot eval @ 2026-03-24T23:59:59Z) is dominated by backlog concentration in two GPU-family partitions, while several other partitions appear fully utilized without accumulating a queue.\n\nWhere pending jobs are concentrated (queueing pain):\n- mi3001x: 36 pending (largest backlog)\n- mi2104x: 26 pending (second-largest backlog)\n- All other partitions are marginal at this snapshot (≤2 pending).\n\nWhich GPU families/partitions look saturated (utilization pressure):\n- Full saturation (partitionCpuSaturation = 1.0): mi3008x, mi3258x, mi3508x. These partitions are running “hot” (at least in CPU terms) even though they are not showing a large pending queue.\n- High but not full: mi3001x (0.75) and mi2104x (~0.619), plus mi2508x (0.7) and staff (~0.656).\n- Low: devel (0.25).\n\nImplications (bottleneck vs imbalance):\n- Primary capacity bottleneck signal is specific to mi3001x and mi2104x: large pending backlogs indicate demand exceeding available capacity or eligibility in those partitions.\n- The pattern “saturated but low pending” (mi3008x/mi3258x/mi3508x) is consistent with steady-state high utilization where demand is being served without building a visible queue at the evaluation time, or where policy/limits/priority shape queue visibility.\n- Possible scheduling/constraint imbalance (lower-confidence): if mi3008x/mi3258x/mi3508x are viable substitutes for mi3001x/mi2104x workloads, the backlog concentration could reflect hard constraints (GRES count, topology, memory, features, partition access) rather than pure cluster-wide scarcity. Confirming requires job constraint/QOS/account data (not in this preview).\n\nConfidence notes (given this panel supports the workspace’s job-correlation focus): the backlog concentrations are strong evidence; however, the saturation metric shown is CPU-based, not explicitly GPU allocation/utilization, so treat “GPU family saturation” as indicative rather than definitive until GPU/GRES allocation metrics are joined in the refreshed job-correlation run."
    ],
    "highlights": [
      "Backlog is highly concentrated: mi3001x=36 pending and mi2104x=26 pending; other partitions are ≤2 pending at the snapshot.",
